Abdul Sattar Edhi, a humanitarian from Pakistan, passed away. He and his wife created a network of social services, including medical clinics, nursing homes, orphanages, soup kitchens, and rehabilitation centers. They also established the largest voluntary ambulance fleet in the world. Edhi dedicated his life to serving others and providing equal treatment for everyone, regardless of nationality, ethnicity, religion, or class. His work stands as a rebuke to those who use fear and violence to create divisions. Condolences are offered to his family, the millions of people whose lives he touched, and the people of Pakistan.